1
00:00:07,577 --> 00:00:09,177
<b>(Episode 21)</b>

2
00:00:10,577 --> 00:00:13,416
<b>Welcome home, girls.</b>

3
00:00:13,716 --> 00:00:15,917
<b>Gosh, Ms. Park.</b>

4
00:00:16,117 --> 00:00:17,617
<b>This is why you told us
to come an hour later.</b>

5
00:00:17,617 --> 00:00:19,386
<b>Did you prepare all these yourself?</b>

6
00:00:19,386 --> 00:00:21,427
<b>I just blew up a few balloons,
that's all.</b>

7
00:00:21,427 --> 00:00:23,357
<b>Goodness, how many balloons
did you blow up?</b>

8
00:00:23,357 --> 00:00:25,026
<b>Ha Jin, do you like it?</b>

9
00:00:25,026 --> 00:00:26,697
<b>I love it.</b>

10
00:00:26,896 --> 00:00:29,166
<b>Ms. Park, you must have taken
an interest in surprising people.</b>

11
00:00:29,166 --> 00:00:30,267
<b>Wait till you go upstairs.</b>

12
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:31,866
<b>I redecorated everything
just in case...</b>

13
00:00:31,866 --> 00:00:33,006
<b>something brings back bad memories.</b>

14
00:00:33,006 --> 00:00:35,407
<b>Don't worry about that.
I already forgot everything.</b>

15
00:00:57,997 --> 00:00:58,997
<b>What do you think?</b>

16
00:00:59,127 --> 00:01:00,266
<b>It's so pretty.</b>

17
00:01:00,266 --> 00:01:01,627
<b>I like this much better than before.</b>

18
00:01:01,627 --> 00:01:03,037
<b>I'm glad.</b>

19
00:01:03,037 --> 00:01:04,766
<b>I put in a bit of an effort.</b>

20
00:01:06,237 --> 00:01:08,466
<b>Get some rest. I need to take this.</b>

21
00:01:12,037 --> 00:01:13,246
<b>Are you sure you're okay?</b>

22
00:01:13,246 --> 00:01:16,047
<b>Of course. There's no reason
for me not to be okay.</b>

23
00:01:16,446 --> 00:01:18,476
<b>You should unpack and get some rest.
I need to rest too.</b>

24
00:01:18,677 --> 00:01:19,687
<b>Okay.</b>

25
00:01:20,317 --> 00:01:21,317
<b>Get some rest.</b>

26
00:01:57,256 --> 00:01:58,256
<b>Ha Jin.</b>

27
00:01:59,386 --> 00:02:01,256
<b>What's going on?
What's with that face?</b>

28
00:02:01,987 --> 00:02:03,896
<b>- What is?
- You were making an odd face.</b>

29
00:02:03,896 --> 00:02:05,297
<b>You were touching your lips and all.</b>

30
00:02:05,797 --> 00:02:07,166
<b>When? I didn't do that.</b>

31
00:02:07,166 --> 00:02:08,267
<b>You seem suspicious.</b>

32
00:02:08,666 --> 00:02:10,037
<b>Very suspicious.</b>

33
00:02:11,336 --> 00:02:13,237
<b>No, it's nothing. What is it?</b>

34
00:02:13,237 --> 00:02:15,706
<b>Right. We're getting
some sandwiches.</b>

35
00:02:15,706 --> 00:02:17,377
<b>- Do you want one?
- Yes, I do.</b>

36
00:02:17,377 --> 00:02:18,777
<b>Okay. Bacon and egg?</b>

37
00:02:18,777 --> 00:02:19,777
<b>Yes.</b>

38
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:05,386
<b>(Find Me in Your Memory)</b>

39
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:33,647
<b>What's the point of coming
to see me? It does nothing good.</b>

40
00:03:33,647 --> 00:03:34,886
<b>You're only ruining my day.</b>

41
00:03:37,117 --> 00:03:38,117
<b>What?</b>

42
00:03:38,117 --> 00:03:40,587
<b>Did you want to see how frustrated
I was to be locked up here?</b>

43
00:03:44,456 --> 00:03:47,426
<b>Too bad. I'm perfectly fine.</b>

44
00:03:48,397 --> 00:03:50,837
<b>Ha Jin will come to me in the end...</b>

45
00:03:52,537 --> 00:03:55,976
<b>once she finds out that you're
her best friend's boyfriend.</b>

46
00:04:01,147 --> 00:04:05,347
<b>I'm here to tell you
there's nothing you can do in there.</b>

47
00:04:07,587 --> 00:04:08,717
<b>Listen up.</b>

48
00:04:09,486 --> 00:04:13,256
<b>First of all, you'll be in prison
a lot longer than you think.</b>

49
00:04:13,356 --> 00:04:14,886
<b>I'll make that happen.</b>

50
00:04:20,397 --> 00:04:21,697
<b>Who do you think you are?</b>

51
00:04:24,996 --> 00:04:27,566
<b>No matter what you do,
I'll be released.</b>

52
00:04:28,306 --> 00:04:30,037
<b>The law works that way.</b>

53
00:04:31,507 --> 00:04:34,106
<b>There's no way
you can keep me here forever.</b>

54
00:04:34,106 --> 00:04:36,046
<b>Breaking and entering,
special violence,</b>

55
00:04:36,046 --> 00:04:37,476
<b>confinement, kidnapping...</b>

56
00:04:38,246 --> 00:04:40,546
<b>Those crimes may get you
three years in prison at most,</b>

57
00:04:41,486 --> 00:04:43,157
<b>maybe even less.</b>

58
00:04:44,186 --> 00:04:46,027
<b>But do you really think that's all?</b>

59
00:04:46,757 --> 00:04:47,827
<b>What are you trying to say?</b>

60
00:04:48,856 --> 00:04:50,796
<b>What if you approached
Moon Seong Ho,</b>

61
00:04:50,796 --> 00:04:52,726
<b>who was sentenced to life
for murder,</b>

62
00:04:52,866 --> 00:04:54,566
<b>figured out his methods,</b>

63
00:04:54,827 --> 00:04:57,397
<b>and tried to commit a copycat crime?</b>

64
00:04:58,496 --> 00:05:01,907
<b>How will the law, the press,
and public opinion...</b>

65
00:05:03,176 --> 00:05:04,507
<b>react to that?</b>

66
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:08,947
<b>I'm different from that murderer.</b>

67
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:11,577
<b>All I wanted to do was
tell Ha Jin the truth...</b>

68
00:05:11,577 --> 00:05:13,887
<b>and vow our love.</b>

69
00:05:15,017 --> 00:05:16,887
<b>Do you think
people will believe that?</b>

70
00:05:18,717 --> 00:05:19,986
<b>That's just one of
those delusions...</b>

71
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:22,626
<b>lunatics like Moon Seong Ho
and you have.</b>

72
00:05:25,597 --> 00:05:27,767
<b>No, that's not true.</b>

73
00:05:28,397 --> 00:05:30,066
<b>Never!</b>

74
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:35,337
<b>Fine. You don't have to
either admit it...</b>

75
00:05:35,337 --> 00:05:37,037
<b>or apologize for it.</b>

76
00:05:38,476 --> 00:05:42,147
<b>Just watch your life
get destroyed in there.</b>

77
00:06:08,306 --> 00:06:09,537
<b>Hello, Anchor Lee.</b>

78
00:06:10,777 --> 00:06:12,077
<b>You were sleeping?</b>

79
00:06:13,546 --> 00:06:17,316
<b>This stuffed animal you gave me
is really effective.</b>

80
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:20,587
<b>I hugged it for a second
and fell asleep right away.</b>

81
00:06:22,087 --> 00:06:23,856
<b>I'm glad to hear that.</b>

82
00:06:24,856 --> 00:06:26,726
<b>Did you get home safely?</b>

83
00:06:26,726 --> 00:06:27,957
<b>Yes, I'm home now.</b>

84
00:06:28,426 --> 00:06:30,757
<b>It's so nice to be back home.</b>

85
00:06:31,356 --> 00:06:33,296
<b>Everything is finally over.</b>

86
00:06:35,226 --> 00:06:37,037
<b>Are you on your way to work?</b>

87
00:06:37,496 --> 00:06:39,537
<b>Yes, I am.</b>

88
00:06:40,507 --> 00:06:41,666
<b>Go back to sleep then.</b>

89
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:44,306
<b>Hold on.</b>

90
00:06:44,976 --> 00:06:47,546
<b>We can talk some more.
I've rested enough.</b>

91
00:06:49,717 --> 00:06:51,316
<b>Can we meet today?</b>

92
00:06:51,447 --> 00:06:53,616
<b>I really need your help
with my script.</b>

93
00:06:53,616 --> 00:06:55,087
<b>The read-through is coming up.</b>

94
00:06:56,757 --> 00:06:57,856
<b>All right.</b>

95
00:06:57,856 --> 00:07:01,157
<b>But on weekdays,
I can only meet after the news.</b>

96
00:07:01,356 --> 00:07:04,356
<b>Is that okay with you?
It'll be pretty late.</b>

97
00:07:04,626 --> 00:07:06,527
<b>Don't worry, I'm a night owl.</b>

98
00:07:07,197 --> 00:07:09,666
<b>Then shall we meet
after the news tonight?</b>

99
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:11,066
<b>I'll come to you.</b>

100
00:07:11,597 --> 00:07:12,707
<b>Okay, let's do that.</b>

101
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,606
<b>Drive safe. See you later.</b>

102
00:07:18,907 --> 00:07:20,277
<b>I don't have time for this.</b>

103
00:07:24,517 --> 00:07:26,147
<b>Sandwiches are here...</b>

104
00:07:30,986 --> 00:07:33,056
<b>What are you doing?
You're going somewhere?</b>

105
00:07:33,257 --> 00:07:35,726
<b>I'm meeting Anchor Lee
for some practice later.</b>

106
00:07:35,856 --> 00:07:38,126
<b>- When?
- After his news.</b>

107
00:07:38,126 --> 00:07:39,926
<b>It's only 10 a.m.</b>

108
00:07:39,926 --> 00:07:42,597
<b>You have 14 hours, and you're
already picking out an outfit?</b>

109
00:07:42,597 --> 00:07:44,467
<b>I want to get a head start.</b>

110
00:07:44,637 --> 00:07:46,436
<b>You're going to make a mess
for the next 14 hours, aren't you?</b>

111
00:07:48,606 --> 00:07:49,676
<b>The thing is...</b>

112
00:07:51,007 --> 00:07:52,037
<b>Come here.</b>

113
00:07:52,037 --> 00:07:53,847
<b>What? What is it now?</b>

114
00:07:57,447 --> 00:07:59,416
<b>It's happening for real.</b>

115
00:07:59,816 --> 00:08:00,816
<b>What do you mean?</b>

116
00:08:00,816 --> 00:08:03,157
<b>Anchor Lee and I are dating
for real now.</b>

117
00:08:04,486 --> 00:08:05,486
<b>You are?</b>

118
00:08:05,816 --> 00:08:07,186
<b>It's true.</b>

119
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:10,157
<b>Sure. Just don't go overboard
and get dumped later.</b>

120
00:08:10,157 --> 00:08:11,957
<b>I'm sure of it. Believe me.</b>

121
00:08:11,957 --> 00:08:13,327
<b>It's happening for real, I swear.</b>

122
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:17,236
<b>What are you doing with your lips?</b>

123
00:08:18,837 --> 00:08:20,907
<b>What? What happened between you two?</b>

124
00:08:22,566 --> 00:08:23,707
<b>You guys kissed?</b>

125
00:08:31,546 --> 00:08:32,717
<b>That hurts!</b>

126
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:37,716
<b>That's what happened.</b>

127
00:08:52,137 --> 00:08:53,936
<b>Are you in the lobby yet?</b>

128
00:08:54,537 --> 00:08:57,537
<b>The cafe in the lobby has
amazing honey black tea.</b>

129
00:08:57,537 --> 00:09:00,306
<b>I highly recommend it.
Get a cup on your way.</b>

130
00:09:00,777 --> 00:09:02,676
<b>Have a nice day. See you later.</b>

131
00:09:03,617 --> 00:09:05,977
<b>I almost forgot.
If you run into Mr. Kim,</b>

132
00:09:05,977 --> 00:09:08,647
<b>please thank him for visiting me
in the hospital the other day.</b>

133
00:09:08,647 --> 00:09:10,357
<b>(Please thank him for visiting me
in the hospital the other day.)</b>

134
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:17,426
<b>Gosh, this is unbelievable.</b>

135
00:09:17,857 --> 00:09:20,166
<b>After all this wait,</b>

136
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:22,426
<b>you finally won his heart.</b>

137
00:09:22,997 --> 00:09:24,997
<b>It'd be more accurate to say...</b>

138
00:09:24,997 --> 00:09:27,607
<b>that Anchor Lee finally realized
his feelings.</b>

139
00:09:28,407 --> 00:09:30,277
<b>So? Are you happy?</b>

140
00:09:31,407 --> 00:09:32,607
<b>Yes, I really am.</b>

141
00:09:34,977 --> 00:09:37,916
<b>Right, weren't you and Mr. Jo
going to work out together?</b>

142
00:09:38,017 --> 00:09:39,716
<b>When are you starting?
Your shoulder is fine now.</b>

143
00:09:39,716 --> 00:09:41,387
<b>We're starting today.</b>

144
00:09:43,086 --> 00:09:44,387
<b>Be honest.</b>

145
00:09:44,956 --> 00:09:46,627
<b>Is something going on
between you two?</b>

146
00:09:47,056 --> 00:09:49,056
<b>What are you talking about?</b>

147
00:09:49,127 --> 00:09:52,497
<b>He got dumped because
he's too weak, so I'm helping him.</b>

148
00:09:53,027 --> 00:09:54,027
<b>Really?</b>

149
00:09:54,267 --> 00:09:57,166
<b>I think you two would make
a cute couple. Too bad.</b>

150
00:09:57,166 --> 00:09:59,436
<b>Don't be ridiculous.</b>

151
00:10:01,436 --> 00:10:03,137
<b>Do you really think...</b>

152
00:10:04,306 --> 00:10:05,336
<b>we'd make a cute couple?</b>

153
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:07,346
<b>He and I?</b>

154
00:10:07,676 --> 00:10:09,546
<b>Yes, I do.</b>

155
00:10:09,747 --> 00:10:10,777
<b>I see.</b>

156
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:13,416
<b>Well...</b>

157
00:10:14,117 --> 00:10:16,387
<b>Why? What makes you think so?</b>

158
00:10:18,857 --> 00:10:22,157
<b>You two have the ideal
height difference and all.</b>

159
00:10:23,096 --> 00:10:24,696
<b>What? Why are you asking?</b>

160
00:10:25,296 --> 00:10:26,997
<b>- I was just curious.
- Are you interested in him?</b>

161
00:10:26,997 --> 00:10:28,426
<b>Don't be ridiculous.</b>

162
00:10:28,426 --> 00:10:30,196
<b>- Why are you stuttering?
- It's not like that.</b>

163
00:10:30,196 --> 00:10:31,196
<b>Your voice is shaking.</b>

164
00:10:31,196 --> 00:10:32,637
<b>I said, no!</b>

165
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,066
<b>- Good morning.
- Good morning.</b>

166
00:10:38,877 --> 00:10:39,946
<b>Good morning, Anchor Lee.</b>

167
00:10:39,946 --> 00:10:41,107
<b>Good morning.</b>

168
00:10:41,907 --> 00:10:45,977
<b>You look like you're in a good mood.
I'm devastated.</b>

169
00:10:48,517 --> 00:10:50,757
<b>What's wrong? Did something happen?</b>

170
00:10:50,757 --> 00:10:54,387
<b>Because he switched you out
the other day,</b>

171
00:10:54,627 --> 00:10:56,926
<b>he, you, and the director
will be disciplined.</b>

172
00:10:57,326 --> 00:10:59,997
<b>Not only me but you two as well?</b>

173
00:10:59,997 --> 00:11:01,127
<b>Unfortunately, yes.</b>

174
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:05,566
<b>The news still has to air,
so you and I will be fine.</b>

175
00:11:05,596 --> 00:11:08,436
<b>But Director Choi will be suspended
until the disciplinary committee...</b>

176
00:11:08,436 --> 00:11:09,737
<b>makes a decision.</b>

177
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:12,507
<b>She's been told to stay
out of his office from today.</b>

178
00:11:13,446 --> 00:11:15,607
<b>What if she ends up getting fired?</b>

179
00:11:15,777 --> 00:11:17,377
<b>But why the director?</b>

180
00:11:17,716 --> 00:11:19,446
<b>I'm the one who is responsible for
what happened.</b>

181
00:11:19,446 --> 00:11:20,586
<b>It doesn't make sense.</b>

182
00:11:20,586 --> 00:11:22,316
<b>What do you mean,
it doesn't make sense?</b>

183
00:11:22,316 --> 00:11:25,586
<b>We switched the anchor out without
reporting it to the higher-ups.</b>

184
00:11:25,916 --> 00:11:28,887
<b>Also, this isn't only about
what happened that day.</b>

185
00:11:28,887 --> 00:11:31,426
<b>Think of all the things
you've revealed...</b>

186
00:11:31,426 --> 00:11:35,426
<b>on the news so far,
ignoring the higher-ups.</b>

187
00:11:35,426 --> 00:11:37,737
<b>You've gotten on their wrong side.</b>

188
00:11:38,596 --> 00:11:40,637
<b>This is just an excuse
to bring you down.</b>

189
00:11:42,066 --> 00:11:43,477
<b>I'm sorry, Mr. Kim.</b>

190
00:11:44,176 --> 00:11:45,537
<b>Where is Director Choi now?</b>

191
00:11:53,387 --> 00:11:54,517
<b>Come in.</b>

192
00:11:56,387 --> 00:11:57,456
<b>Director Choi.</b>

193
00:12:03,796 --> 00:12:05,956
<b>Judging by your face,
I guess you heard the news.</b>

194
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:09,637
<b>It's no big deal.
Don't worry and go back to work.</b>

195
00:12:10,296 --> 00:12:11,666
<b>I apologize.</b>

196
00:12:13,537 --> 00:12:14,966
<b>For what?</b>

197
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:18,507
<b>For trying to save someone close
to you who got kidnapped?</b>

198
00:12:18,607 --> 00:12:19,806
<b>Or is it because you left...</b>

199
00:12:20,407 --> 00:12:24,176
<b>after only asking for my permission
instead of following protocol...</b>

200
00:12:25,277 --> 00:12:26,647
<b>and asking everyone in management?</b>

201
00:12:30,257 --> 00:12:34,086
<b>It was only a natural thing to do.
So why would you apologize?</b>

202
00:12:35,157 --> 00:12:38,397
<b>I caused you and
the team manager trouble.</b>

203
00:12:38,397 --> 00:12:41,426
<b>We switched the main anchor out
without any prior notice.</b>

204
00:12:41,426 --> 00:12:43,336
<b>We should take responsibility
for that.</b>

205
00:12:43,436 --> 00:12:47,206
<b>But that's it.
Don't read anything more into it.</b>

206
00:12:47,966 --> 00:12:51,576
<b>I'll try to explain it
to the president in person.</b>

207
00:12:51,576 --> 00:12:54,377
<b>Gosh, you talk too much.</b>

208
00:12:54,706 --> 00:12:56,877
<b>Don't you trust me?</b>

209
00:12:57,176 --> 00:13:00,086
<b>What are you talking about?
You know how much I look up to you.</b>

210
00:13:00,086 --> 00:13:03,186
<b>Then just let it go
when I tell you everything's cool.</b>

211
00:13:03,657 --> 00:13:07,086
<b>Also, consider yourself lucky
to have an amazing boss like me,</b>

212
00:13:07,086 --> 00:13:08,157
<b>okay?</b>

213
00:13:08,527 --> 00:13:11,127
<b>Besides, the disciplinary
committee's decision...</b>

214
00:13:11,127 --> 00:13:13,066
<b>will come in 3 or 4 days
at the latest.</b>

215
00:13:13,296 --> 00:13:16,596
<b>I think I'm going to take
this chance and take some time off.</b>

216
00:13:16,596 --> 00:13:18,897
<b>So leave me alone and get out.</b>

217
00:13:25,877 --> 00:13:27,306
<b>I'm sorry, Director Choi.</b>

218
00:13:28,107 --> 00:13:29,346
<b>All right.</b>

219
00:13:32,816 --> 00:13:34,346
<b>I love you, Director Choi.</b>

220
00:13:35,747 --> 00:13:36,816
<b>Thanks.</b>

221
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,666
<b>Gosh, I've never had a break before.</b>

222
00:13:49,426 --> 00:13:52,196
<b>I mean,
I rarely get to take a break.</b>

223
00:13:52,537 --> 00:13:54,936
<b>Why am I reading the newspaper? Why?</b>

224
00:13:54,936 --> 00:13:56,507
